\subsection{Spontaneous decay dynamics}
Relations (\ref{2})-(\ref{6}) allow calculating the time-dependent population of any Zeeman sublevel of any atom in an ensemble. Here we will analyze the decay of an initially populated sublevel $J=1,\;m=-1$ of central atom. For brevity we denote the amplitude of this state as $b_{0}(t)$. The corresponding population $P_0(t)$ can be found as follows

